        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10184",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "What would this offer beyond the query caches already included with many RDBMS?\n\nThis trades the query cache system in a RDBMS for a different caching system (e.g. local file-based, or memcache).\n\nWith the use of MVC, there are other abstractions to consider caching, including logical models constructed from processing data retrieved from the DB.\n\nCache expiration becomes problematic.  When to expire what data in the cache?\n\nIf all DB commits pass through the cache system logic first, then the cache can mark items \"dirty\".\nIf not, then we need some other approach, such as TTL (time-to-live) which result in \"imperfect\" results (stale data returned by the cache).",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-06-27T19:33:35.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-06-27T19:33:35.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10186",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=munzili",
                        "name": "munzili",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Munz",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "You can simply check it based on the table name. For caching on localy file, you can use a permanent SQLite Connection. \n\nHere an example script ( this is an extension for the PEAR::DB Class ) that i wrote some time ago: \n[http:\/\/pear.php.net\/pepr\/pepr-proposal-show.php?id=357]\n[http:\/\/schulermanager.at\/pear\/DB_cache_pgsql.phps]\n\nYou can use the same system\/idea here.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=munzili",
                        "name": "munzili",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Munz",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-06-28T01:59:45.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-06-28T01:59:45.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10193",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I think something of this size and complexity should follow the [normal proposal process|http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/wiki\/display\/ZFPROP\/Home].",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
