                    "created": "2006-06-28T17:43:28.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-06-28T17:43:28.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10198",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=munzili",
                        "name": "munzili",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Munz",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Well, as far as i know, the proposal is for creating new addongs\/Core modul. But this shouldn't be an addon or so on. It should be integreated into the Zend_Db class. Or do you think, its better to create a new class for this also, like: Zend_Db_Cache? In my opinion, its not nessesary to create a new Proporsal, but if needed ( for managment issues\/structure ), i can register as a Programmer and take care of this proporsal.",
